---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Bulk Custom T-Shirt Event Needs | The Ultimate Guide">
  <article class="blog-post">
    <header class="post-header text-center animate-up">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="meta text-secondary mb-2">Event Planning • 8 Min Read</div>
        <h1>The Ultimate Guide to Finding the Perfect Place for Your Bulk Custom T-Shirt Event Needs</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-secondary lead">Organizing a large event? Learn exactly what to look for when choosing a print partner for bulk orders to ensure everything arrives flawlessly and on time.</p>
        <div class="author mt-4">By the Lialvaro Team</div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container post-content animate-up delay-1">
      <p>Planning an event is stressful enough without worrying if the merchandise or volunteer uniforms will look right—or arrive on time. Whether it's a corporate retreat in Downtown LA, a marathon, or a massive music festival, your bulk t-shirt order is a critical component of the event's professional image.</p>

      <h2>1. Prioritize Communication</h2>
      <p>When dealing with hundreds or thousands of garments, you cannot afford to work with a "submit your file and hope for the best" online portal. You need a dedicated partner. Look for print shops that offer phone support and real aesthetic guidance before the ink hits the fabric. A good printer will evaluate your artwork, suggest the best garment style, and warn you of potential print issues early on.</p>

      <h2>2. Insist on Screen Printing for Scale</h2>
      <p>While DTG (Direct to Garment) is amazing for small batches, bulk orders require <strong>Screen Printing</strong>. It is the gold standard for high-volume jobs because it's significantly faster per shirt and the cost plummets as quantity increases. Furthermore, screen printing delivers that vibrant, tactile feel that event-goers love to wear for years to come.</p>

      <h2>3. Ask About Capacity and Deadlines</h2>
      <p>Can the shop handle an order of 2,000 shirts in 7 days? Some boutique shops max out at a few hundred shirts a week. Always clearly state your absolute drop-dead date before signing off on a quote. Shops that handle all printing in-house (rather than outsourcing) have total control over their schedule and are much more reliable.</p>

      <h2>4. Request a Sample or Proof</h2>
      <p>Never run a bulk order completely blind. Ask for a digital mock-up, or even better, a physical printed sample if time permits. Seeing the pantone colors on the actual fabric type you selected can save you from a massive, costly disappointment.</p>

      <h2>5. Delivery Logistics</h2>
      <p>Shipping 50 massive boxes of shirts across the country is expensive and risky. If your event is in Los Angeles, partner with a Los Angeles-based printer like Lialvaro Apparel. We frequently work with local event coordinators, offering direct-to-venue delivery, bypassing shipping headaches entirely.</p>

      <div class="post-cta text-center mt-4">
        <h3>Planning an event in LA?</h3>
        <p class="mb-2">Let us handle the merchandising so you can focus on the event itself.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="button primary">Get a Bulk Order Quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .post-header { padding: 140px 0 60px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-primary) 0%, var(--bg-secondary) 100%); }
  .post-header h1 { font-size: 3.5rem; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .meta { font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; font-size: 0.9rem;}
  .lead { font-size: 1.5rem; max-width: 700px; margin: 1rem auto; line-height: 1.6; }
  .author { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); }

  .post-content { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 20px 8rem; }
  .post-content p { font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #a1a1a6; }
  .post-content h2 { margin: 4rem 0 1.5rem; font-size: 2.25rem; color: var(--text-primary); letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  
  .post-content ul { margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #a1a1a6; padding-left: 2rem; line-height: 1.8; }
  .post-content ul li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .post-content strong { color: var(--text-primary); }

  .post-cta { padding: 4rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border-radius: 24px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin-top: 4rem; }
  .post-cta h3 { font-size: 2.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .post-header { padding: 100px 0 40px; }
    .post-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; }
    .lead { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    .post-content p, .post-content ul { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .post-content h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
    .post-cta { padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>
